Why this set works (no bloat)

Each engine answers a distinct question:

Engine	Question
NTE	What could this be?
T·J·P	Is it strong?
RNE	Is it true?
DAE	How does it spread?
REE	Who executes it?
FLE	Did it work?
PME	Can we reuse it?
AME	What matters next?

No overlap. No redundancy.

⸻

Key principle (important)

Engines should map to bottlenecks, not ideas

Right now bottlenecks are:
	•	attention
	•	distribution
	•	iteration speed
	•	reuse

These engines directly attack those.

⸻

If you only add 2 (highest ROI)

Start with:
	1.	DAE (Distribution)
	2.	FLE (Feedback)

Because:

Without distribution → nothing happens
Without feedback → nothing improves

